imdb.title: Soul Eater Not!
imdb.plot: "Soul Eater Not!" is a spin off series from the main series "Soul Eater". Tsugumi Harudori from the NOT class must choose between Anya and Meme for a partner, while fighting a dangerous foe.

episodes.title: Enrolling at the DWMA!
episodes.plot: When 14-year-old middle-schooler Tsugumi Harudori discovers she is a weapon, she flies to America to enroll at DWMA. There, she meets the absent-minded Meme Tatane and the patrician Anya Hepburn, both of whom are meisters that are also new enrollees.

episodes.title: Girls' Dorm á la Carte!
episodes.plot: Fellow student Eternal Feather shows Tsugumi, Meme and Anya around the girls' dorm, and they meet some of the residents there. By the next morning, all three had lost their allowance, and thus had to take part-time jobs at a café named "Deathbucks."

episodes.title: The Witch of the Girls' Dorm!
episodes.plot: Eternal Feather reveals more about Kim's history, as well as the origin of her name. A new threat, known as "Traitor," menaces the students of DWMA, and Sid sends Clay and Akane to scare them off. Anya feels left out when she misses her turn with Tsugumi.

episodes.title: Waver, Run!
episodes.plot: After a nightmare, Tsugumi wonders why the meisters choose to come to DWMA. She spends some time talking to Akane, who asks her to be his girlfriend, only to say he was joking. The class takes their physical fitness exams, where both Meme and Anya excel.

episodes.title: Invitation Fighting!
episodes.plot: After dreaming about Kim, Jacqueline is bothered by feelings of attraction for her. Kim leads the girls in a pool-cleaning job, and after she takes most of the pay, they help Jacqueline try to win Kim over, while learning about her mysterious background.

episodes.title: This Is a Real Fight!
episodes.plot: Liz and Patty Thompson take jobs as waitresses at Deathbucks, and manage to scare off much of the clientele, including Meme and Anya. However, Tsugumi sees something in them, and fights to keep going to the café, determined to become more like them.

episodes.title: Nice Day for a Death Bazaar!
episodes.plot: Clay's investigation into the Traitors narrows down Shaula Gorgon as a likely suspect. The NOT class girls have a study session at Deathbucks. Later, the girls attend the Death Bazaar free market, where Eternal Feather's unlucky streak turns grim.

episodes.title: Tsugumi Spiral!
episodes.plot: Dr. Stein is able to save Eternal Feather's life, and teases our heroines as she recovers. Tsugumi and Meme share some Japanese ways to keep cool in the summer. Tsugumi laments not being able to defend her meister, which is why she hasn't chosen one.

episodes.title: Pumpkin Growing!
episodes.plot: A collection of four short stories chronicles the passing of summer, as the girls grow pumpkins for Halloween. A hot night spells trouble sleeping. Meme has a short-term memory misadventure. Tsugumi teaches Anya about baseball. The girls each write home.

episodes.title: The Beginning of the Nightmare!
episodes.plot: Tsugumi is devastated by news of her pet dog's death. She lashes out at Meme, who later that night sleepwalks to DWMA. Meme is suspected of being controlled by Shaula, and placed in DWMA custody. When Anya and Tsugumi visit, things soon get out of hand!

episodes.title: Their Various Resolves!
episodes.plot: Anya, under escort by Clay and Akane, passes the Battle Festival grounds, where Shaula's followers attack! Tsugumi also flees house arrest to try to meet up with Anya, so together they can save Meme. Dr. Stein works on an antidote to Shaula's poison.

episodes.title: Soul Resonance!
episodes.plot: With the antidote in hand, Tsugumi and Anya fight desperately to release Meme from Shaula's mind control. The fighting spreads throughout town, until it even reaches the girls' dorm. Tsugumi comes to a decision that will affect all three of their lives.
